com.samsung.android.sdk.pen.document

Class SpenPageDoc

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.samsung.android.sdk.pen.document.SpenPageDoc

  • public final class SpenPageDoc
extends Object
    Page document Class
    This class contains all the data in a page. It manages the objects in the page and provides the command history for undo and redo commands.

      • appendObject

        public void appendObject(SpenObjectBase object)
        Add the specified object to the current layer of the page document.
        The add object action is recorded in the history stack. 
         ObjectImage image = pagedoc.createObject(SpenObjectBase.TYPE_IMAGE);
 image.setImage(bitmap); // Nothing is appended, nothing to be recorded to history.
 page.appendObject(image);
 image.setImage(bitmap2); // Object is appended, record actions to history.
        Parameters:
        object - The object that you want to add.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - Thrown if the object has already been added.
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if the object passed is null.

      • insertObject

        public void insertObject(SpenObjectBase object,
                int index)
        Insert the specified object at the specified index in the current layer of the page document.
        The insert object action is recorded in the history stack. 
         ObjectImage image = pagedoc.createObject(SpenObjectBase.TYPE_IMAGE);
 image.setImage(bitmap); // Nothing is appended, nothing to be recorded to history.
 page.insertObject(image, 1);
 image.setImage(bitmap2); // Object is inserted, record actions to history.
        Parameters:
        object - The object that you want to insert.
        index - The index where the object is inserted.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - Thrown if the index is larger than the number of objects or smaller than 0.
        IllegalStateException - Thrown if the object has already been added.
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if the object passed is null.

      • removeObject

        public void removeObject(SpenObjectBase object)
        Remove the specified object from the current layer of the page document.
        If the object is on the selected object list, this method removes it from that list.
        The remove object's action is not recorded in the history stack.
        Parameters:
        object - The object that you want to remove.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - Thrown if the page document is not loaded.
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if the object passed is null.
        See Also:
        selectObject(ArrayList), getSelectedObject()

      • findObjectInClosedCurve

        public ArrayList<SpenObjectBase> findObjectInClosedCurve(int typeFilter,
                                                PointF[] points)
        Find the objects of the specified type contained in the closed curves defined by the specified points.
        The points connect the curve in order.
        If the curve does not intersect, this method connects the first point and the last point.
        If two points overlap, one of them is ignored and the next point is connected.
        Objects within object containers cannot be found.
        Parameters:
        typeFilter - The object filter.
        For example:
        findObjectInClosedCurve(PageDoc.FIND_TYPE_STROKE|PageDoc.FIND_TYPE_IMAGE, points)
        The valid values are:
        FIND_TYPE_STROKE
        FIND_TYPE_IMAGE
        FIND_TYPE_TEXT_BOX
        FIND_TYPE_CONTAINER
        FIND_TYPE_ALL
        points - The point array that defines the curves.
        Returns:
        The object list
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if the arguments passed are invalid.

      • groupObject

        public SpenObjectContainer groupObject(ArrayList<SpenObjectBase> groupList,
                              boolean selectAfterGroup)
        Group the objects in the specified list.
        This method puts the grouped list in an SpenObjectContainer. This method sorts the objects in the stacking order on the layer.
        This method moves the objects into SpenObjectContainer from the layer.
        The new SpenObjectContainer comes to the front layer.
        The objects in the specified groupList are removed from the current layer.
        The index of SpenObjectContainer is the biggest index value in groupList. 
         For example:
 The page has s1,s2,s3,s4,s5,s6,s7,s8.
 
 ArrayList list = new ArrayList();
 list.add(s2);
 list.add(s7);
 list.add(s4);
 ObjectContainer container = page.groupObject(list,false);
 container.getObject(0) is the s2.
 container.getObject(1) is the s4.
 container.getObject(2) is the s7.
 
 The object list is s1,s3,s5,s6,container,s8.
        You can also create an object group without using the method above as shown below. 
         For example:
 The page has s1,s2,s3,s4,s5,s6,s7,s8.
 
 pagedoc.removeObject(s2);
 pagedoc.removeObject(s4);
 int index_s7 = pagedoc.getObjectIndex(s7);
 pagedoc.removeObject(s7);
 
 ObjectContainer container = pagedoc.createObject(SpenObjectBase.TYPE_CONTAINER);
 container.appendObject(s2);
 container.appendObject(s4);
 container.appendObject(s7);
 
 pagedoc.insertObject(container, index_s7);
 
 The object list is s1,s3,s5,s6,container,s8.
        Parameters:
        groupList - The object list that you want to group.
        selectAfterGroup - Set to true to select the new container after grouping, set to false to not select the new container after grouping.
        Returns:
        The new SpenObjectContainer.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if the groupList passed includes a non-existent object or if the size of the list is less than 2.
        IllegalStateException - Thrown if the page document is not loaded.

      • groupSelectedObject

        See Also:

      • ungroupObject

        public void ungroupObject(SpenObjectContainer group,
                 boolean selectAfterUngroup)
        Ungroup the objects in the specified group.
        This method breaks down the SpenObjectContainer in the current layer into objects and inserts the objects in the stacking order in the container. 
         For example:
 The page has s1,s2,s3,s4,s5,s6,s7,s8.
 
 ArrayList list = new ArrayList();
 list.add(s2);
 list.add(s7);
 list.add(s4);
 ObjectContainer container = page.groupObject(list,false);
 container.getObject(0) is the s2.
 container.getObject(1) is the s4.
 container.getObject(2) is the s7.
 
 The page has s1,s3,s5,s6,container,s8.
 
 page.ungroupObject(container,true);
 
 The page has is s1,s3,s5,s6,s2,s4,s7,s8
 
 list = getSelectedObject();
 list.get(0) is the s2.
 list.get(1) is the s4
 list.get(2) is the s7.
        Parameters:
        group - The SpenObjectContainer to ungroup.
        selectAfterUngroup - Set to true to select the ungrouped objects and replace the Selected object list with the ungrouped objects, set to false to not select the ungrouped objects.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if the specified group does not exist in the current layer.
        IllegalStateException - Thrown if the page document is not loaded.

        public void loadObject()
                throws IOException

        Throws:

        See Also:

      • unloadObject

        public void unloadObject()
                  throws IOException
        Unload the objects in the page.
        This method saves the objects and layers on the page in the cache directory and unloads them from memory.
        The unloaded objects cannot be used any more.
        When objects are unloaded, the methods for the objects trigger the loadObject method internally.
        You cannot use methods that receive an unloaded object instance as their parameter.
        The command history stack for the unloaded objects is cleared.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - Thrown if the page is not attached to a note.
        IllegalStateException - Thrown if the isObjectLoaded() method returns false.
        IOException - Thrown if the page file is not found.
        See Also:
        isObjectLoaded(), loadObject()

      • removeLayer

        public void removeLayer(int id)
        Remove the specified layer.
        You cannot remove all the layers.
        If a current layer is removed from the page, the layer in front of the layer becomes the current layer.
        For example, if the current layer is Layer 2 and it is removed, Layer 3 becomes the current layer.
        0 - 1 - [2] - 3 - 4 (currnt layer is 2, removes 2 layer )
        0 - 1 - [3] - 4 (current layer is 3)
        If you call this method after calling the SpenView.setPageDoc(SpenPageDoc, boolean) method, this layer is drawn on SpenView after SpenSurfaceView.update().
        Parameters:
        id - The ID of the layer.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if there is only one layer.

        public void copy(SpenPageDoc sourcePage)

        The objects on the pasted page are resized on the target page. If the width of the pasted page is 720 and that of the target page is 1080, all the objects including rect, point, margin, line spacing, border width, font size and pen size are resized by 150%.

      • isUndoable

        public boolean isUndoable()
        Check if the action is undoable.
        Check if the undo stack in the history manager is empty.
        If it is empty, there is no command to undo, and this method returns false.
        If it is not empty, it returns true.
        Always call this method before calling page.undo(). 
         if (page.isUndoable() == true) {
 spenSurfaceView.updateUndo(page.undo());
 }
        Returns:
        true – if the undo stack is not empty.
        false – if the undo stack is empty.
        See Also:
        undo()

        public boolean isRedoable()

        Check if the redo stack in the history manager is empty.
        If it is empty, there is no command to redo, and the method returns false.
        If it is not empty, it returns true.
        Always use this method before calling page.redo(). 
         if (page.isRedoable() == true) {
 spenSurfaceView.updateRedo(page.redo());
 }
        Returns:
        true – if the redo stack is not empty.
        false – if the redo stack is empty.
        See Also:
        redo()

      • isUndoable

        public boolean isUndoable(int userId)
        Check if the action is undoable for the specified user.
        Check if the undo stack in the history manager for this user is empty.
        If it is empty, there is no command to undo, and the method returns false.
        If it is not empty, it returns true.
        Always use this method before calling page.undo(). 
         if (page.isUndoable(userId) == true) {
 spenMultiView.updateUndo(page.undo(userId),userId);
 }
        Returns:
        true – if the undo stack for the user is not empty. false – if the undo stack for the user is empty.
        See Also:
        undo(int)

      • isRedoable

        public boolean isRedoable(int userId)
        Check if the action is redoable for the specified user.
        Check if the redo stack in the history manager for this user is empty.
        If it is empty, there is no command to redo, and the method returns false.
        If it is not empty, it returns true.
        Always use this method before calling page.redo(). 
         if (page.isRedoable(userId) == true) {
 spenMultiView.updateRedo(page.undo(userId),userId);
 }
        Returns:
        true – if the redo stack for the user is not empty.
        false – if the redo stack for the user is empty.
        See Also:
        redo(int)

      • setUndoLimit

        public void setUndoLimit(int undoLimit)
        Set the limit for the number of undo commands in the undo stack. The default value is 50.
        The 51st command pushes, the first command out of the undo stack of the history manager if the limit is set to 50.
        Use this method to change the limit. 
         page.setUndoLimit(100);
        Parameters:
        undoLimit - The undo command limit.
        See Also:
        getUndoLimit()

      • getUndoLimit

        public int getUndoLimit()
        Get the limit for the undo commands. 
         if (page.getLimit() == 0) {
 page.setUndoLimit(100);
 }
        Returns:
        The limit for the undo commands.
        See Also:
        setUndoLimit(int)

      • commitHistory

        public void commitHistory(SpenPageDoc.HistoryUpdateInfo userData)
        Save the command history for undo and redo.
        To execute undo and redo commands properly and to update the viewport, use this method with SpenView.
        It is recommended that you call SpenView.updata() to create undo and redo data because SpenSurfaceView.updata() calls commitHistory internally.
        Parameters:
        userData - The canvas update data for undo or redo commands.
